eNCA's Ronald Masinda reports. Courtesy of #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - Gyms are safe places and not super-spreader venues. That's the opinion of Fit SA after local and international research has shown gyms have hardly had COVID-19 cases. READ: Level 2 lockdown: Cape Town gyms open for business Since fitness centres reopened in August last year, they've only been allowed to operate at 50 percent capacity. The industry says government must urgently look at changing the regulations. - eNCA's Ronald Masinda reports.